But the Parliamentary Service Commission secured court orders refraining the President from acting on the advisory.Ms Shollei proposes that the 47 county woman representative positions in the National Assembly be scrapped.The bill, which was first introduced in the House on July 24, 2019, will require a plebiscite should the National Assembly and Senate approve it.This is because it directly affects devolution, a protected clause in the constitution that can only be altered through a popular vote.